attribs.name: repeating_attack_-MU6-FHxhqZTisixN2Ln_description
attribs.current:
Tractor Beam
A weapon with this special property can generate a stable beam of gravitons, creating a tractor beam that can move other ships. In addition to dealing damage, a hit with a tractor beam prevents the target ship from moving normally. The gunner can push or pull the target ship (at a rate of 2 hexes per round, resolved at the beginning of the helm phase), or hold the target ship in place. The pilot of the targeted starship can attempt a Piloting check (DC = 15 + 1-1/2  the tier of the firing ship) to break free of the tractor beam as her action in a round. When a tractor beam weapon is locked on to a starship, it cant be used as a regular weapon. A tractor beam is effective only against ships of the same size as the firing ship or smaller; larger ships are unaffected by the tractor beam.

attribs.name: repeating_attack_-MU6-Hyua1mkHKEl8sUW_description
attribs.current:
Point
A weapon with this special property is always short range and cant be fired against targets that are outside the first range increment. If a tracking weapon would hit a ship in an arc that contains a weapon with the point special property, the gunner of the targeted starship can attempt an immediate gunnery check with the point weapon against the incoming tracking projectile using the bonus listed in parentheses in the weapons Special entry (instead of her usual bonus to gunnery checks). The DC for this gunnery check is equal to 10 + the tracking weapons speed. If the attack hits, the tracking weapon is destroyed before it can damage the ship. A point weapon can be used to attempt only one such free gunnery check each round, but this usage potentially allows a point weapon to be fired twice in a single round.

attribs.name: repeating_system_-MU6-Zm2SHgdVa2skqZC_description
attribs.current: Good crew quarters are a bit more upscale than common crew quarters. They consist of dormitory-style rooms that can hold one or two small beds (larger starships usually require lower-ranking crew members to share these quarters) and sometimes a personal closet or drawer space for each occupant. Good crew quarters also include one or two shared bathrooms with multiple sinks and shower stalls, and a dining space with an attached galley. Crews of larger starships eat in this dining space in shifts.

attribs.name: repeating_system_-MU6-vG5SaBArXOkEKIF_description
attribs.current: A brig contains all the necessary restraints and security systems to incarcerate up to eight Medium creatures.

attribs.name: repeating_system_-MU6-wio-ZIwf59xon1m_description
attribs.current: Unconverted expansion bays count as cargo holds. A cargo hold can contain approximately 25 tons of goods, with no item being larger than Large. A starship with multiple cargo holds can hold larger objects; usually 4 contiguous cargo holds are required to hold Huge objects and 8 for Gargantuan objects.

attribs.name: repeating_system_-MU6-yvQgZCZfGr-Gpz7_description
attribs.current: Starships that function as passenger vessels require spaces apart from their crew quarters for their guests to sleep. A single expansion bay can be converted into common quarters (usually simple bunks or hammocks) for six passengers, good quarters (usually a comfortable bed, a desk with a chair, and a small set of drawers) for four passengers, or luxurious quarters (usually a large bed, a wardrobe, a couch, a desk with a nice chair, and a private washroom) for two passengers.

attribs.name: repeating_attack_-MU64E8HWDhBiMkux5QY_description
attribs.current:
When detonated, a flash grenade releases a pulse of intense radiance.

Explode
Explosives have the explode special property, which lists the amount of damage the explosion deals, the damage type, special effects (with a duration, if necessary), and the radius of the explosion. When the Security Specialist attacks with this type of weapon or ammunition, aim at a grid intersection. Each creature within the blast radius takes the listed damage but can attempt a Reflex saving throw for half damage. If the explode special property has any special effects other than damage, they are negated with a successful saving throw. If they score a critical hit, it applies only to the creature closest to the targeted intersection (they choose the creature if several are equally close). Some exploding weapons, such as smoke grenades, dont deal damage, so they dont include the damage and damage type entries.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU64vEXABGdg3bFEFOu_description
attribs.current: The guard fighting style focuses on defence. The New Elysium Security Specialist becomes adept at wearing armour, protecting against attacks, and enduring damage and other setbacks from attacks that get through their defences.

attribs.name: save_notes
attribs.current: +2 vs. Disease, Mind-Affecting Effects, Poison, and Sleep

attribs.name: tactics
attribs.current:
During Combat: Lomer sticks close to Virlae and manifests their solar weapon, a flat club. They make nonlethal attacks with their solar weapon (taking a 4 penalty to each), but they dont use their stellar revelations unless the situation becomes dire.

Morale: Lomer backs down when reduced to fewer than 40 Hit Points, but only if Virlae has also backed down

attribs.name: other_abilities
attribs.current: Constructed, Flat Affect, Solar Manifestation (Solar Weapon), Stellar Alignment, Upgrade Slot (Radiation Buffer), Shadow Manifestations (Shadow Cloak)

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU65wRXxYz0n6HeTBIG_description
attribs.current: When Lomer's fully graviton-attuned, as a standard action, they can pull any number of creatures within 20 feet of them closer. They choose which creatures are affected and which ones arent. Each target must succeed at a Fortitude save or be pulled 10 feet toward them. The range of this revelation and the distance pulled increase by 5 feet at 5th level and every 4 levels thereafter. Solid objects do not block this ability, but any creature that runs into a solid object ceases moving closer to them. Creatures moved by this ability do not provoke attacks of opportunity from this movement. After they use this revelation, they immediately become unattuned. Black hole functions as a zenith revelation for the purposes of abilities that reference them.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU66-lsLo0DHdf7nCaE_description
attribs.current: When Lomer's fully photon-attuned, as a standard action, they can deal 6d6 fire damage to all creatures within 10 feet of them. A creature that succeeds at a Reflex save takes half damage. After they use this revelation, they immediately become unattuned. Supernova functions as a zenith revelation for the purposes of abilities that reference them.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU664KFo8N9jMJ58ky7_description
attribs.current:
As a standard action, Lomer can wreathe themselves in stellar fire and make a charge without the penalties (see page 248).
When they are attuned or fully attuned, they can substitute a bull rush for the melee attack at the end of the charge. If they attempt this bull rush, the target takes 2d6 fire damage (Reflex half), regardless of whether they succeed.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU661icxgAMZD9iYRdy_description
attribs.current: As a move action, Lomer can draw on the properties of dark matter to increase their density, allowing them to resist physical damage. They gain damage reduction 1/. This benefit lasts for 1 round or until they leave graviton mode. When they are attuned or fully attuned, their DR from dark matter is equal to half their solarian level.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MqLUqbJ3pzCDoKPJqSq_description
attribs.current:
Lomer easily blends in with shadows.

Gift: Provided Lomer is in an area of dim light or darkness, they can use Stealth to hide even while being observed.

Stain: Lomer's muscles weaken. When Lomer attempts any Strength-based check, roll twice and take the worse result.

attribs.name: tactics
attribs.current:
During Combat: Virlae doesnt pull any punches and attempts to use trick attack every round.

Morale: Virlae finally backs down when reduced to fewer than 30 Hit Points.

attribs.name: other_abilities
attribs.current: Operative Exploits (Uncanny Mobility, Versatile Movement), Specialization (Daredevil), Shadow Manifestations (Shadow Cloak)

attribs.name: repeating_attack_-MU67TPpRLosuIv-LAtv_description
attribs.current:
This blade looks much like a single-edged survival knife when opened, but the blade can be folded or collapsed to fit within the grip, making it easier to conceal. A switch on the knife means the blade can be folded or extended as a swift action, or as part of making an attack or full attack. Most weapon manufacturers that offer daggers also produce switchblades.

Merciful
A weapon with the merciful fusion often hums pleasantly when at rest and makes soft, airy musical noises when it is used to make an attack. The magic of this fusion subdues the damaging effect of the weapon it is added to. While this fusion is active, the weapons regular damage becomes nonlethal damage. If the weapon deals two types of damage, both of the damage types become nonlethal. Virlae can activate or deactivate the merciful fusion as a swift action.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6804hYOjfrOBr36J0_description
attribs.current:
Vilrae detects the surface thoughts of intelligent creatures around her. The amount of information revealed depends on how long she studies a particular area or target.

1st Round: Vilrae detects the presence or absence of thoughts from conscious creatures that have Intelligence scores of at least 1 (or an Intelligence modifier of 5) or higher.

2nd Round: Vilrae detects the number of thinking minds and the Intelligence score (or modifier) of each. If the highest Intelligence score is 26 (or a modifier of +8) or higher and at least 10 points higher than her own Intelligence score (or 5 points higher than her own Intelligence modifier), she is stunned for 1 round and the spell ends. This spell doesnt let her determine the location of the thinking minds if she cant see the creatures whose thoughts she is detecting.

3rd Round: Vilrae can read the surface thoughts of any mind in the area. A target who succeeds at its Will save prevents her from reading its thoughts, and she must cast detect thoughts again to have another chance. Creatures of animal intelligence (an Intelligence score of 1 or 2 or an Intelligence modifier of 4 or lower) have simple, instinctual thoughts.

Each round, Vilrae can turn to detect thoughts in a new area. The spell can penetrate barriers, but 3 feet of dirt or wood, 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or any force field blocks it.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU9wEZMM6xRTpzm3o6-_description
attribs.current:
This charm makes a humanoid creature regard Rhissona as its trusted friend and ally (treat the targets attitude as friendly). If the creature is currently being threatened or attacked by her or her allies, however, it receives a +5 bonus to its saving throw.

The spell does not enable you to control the charmed creature as if it were an automaton. It is unlikely to attempt to harm her, but it is also unlikely to attack any of its true friends or allies. She can try to give the target suggestions, but she must succeed at an opposed Charisma check to convince it to do anything it wouldnt ordinarily do. (Retries of this check are not allowed.) An affected creature never obeys suicidal or obviously harmful suggestions. Any act by she or her apparent allies that threatens the charmed creature breaks the spell. She must speak the creatures language to communicate her suggestions, or else be good at pantomiming.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU9wIEKuTMH22HwZM4Z_description
attribs.current:

Approach: The target moves toward Rhissona as quickly and directly as possible for 1 round, taking no other actions and triggering reactions (such as attacks of opportunity) for this movement as normal.

Drop: The target drops whatever it is holding. It cant pick up any dropped item until its next turn.

Fall: The target falls to the ground and remains prone for 1 round. It can otherwise act normally.

Flee: The target moves away from Rhissona as quickly and directly as possible for 1 round, taking no other actions and provoking reactions (such as attacks of opportunity) for this movement as normal.

Halt: The target is dazed for 1 round.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6EcUQVzGG4U5OBwmY_description
attribs.current:
The creature or object touched becomes invisible (see page 264). If the target is a creature, any gear it is carrying vanishes as well. If Kofehsu casts the spell on someone else, neither him nor his allies can see the target unless he can normally see invisible things or he employs magic to do so.

The spell ends if the target attacks any creature. For purposes of this spell, an attack includes any spell or harmful effect targeting a foe or whose area or effect includes a foe. Actions directed at unattended objects dont break the spell. Spells that specifically affect allies but not foes are not attacks for this purpose, even when they include foes in their area. Causing harm indirectly is not an attack. Thus, an invisible being can open doors, talk, eat, climb stairs, summon security forces and have them attack, start a trash compactor with foes inside, remotely trigger traps, and so forth.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6EcUQVzGG4U5OBwmY_target
attribs.current: One Creature or Object of No More than 50 Bulk

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6EihwtEMpHRNd2o9z_description
attribs.current: Kofehsu covers a solid surface with a layer of slippery grease. Any creature in the area when the spell is cast must succeed at a Reflex save or fall prone. A creature can walk within or through the area of grease at half normal speed with a successful DC 10 Acrobatics check. Failure means the creature cant move that round and must then succeed at a Reflex save or fall prone, while failure by 5 or more means it falls prone (see the Acrobatics skill on page 135 for details). A creature that doesnt move on its turn doesnt need to attempt this check and isnt considered flat-footed. The spell can also be used to create a greasy coating on an item. Unattended material objects are always affected by this spell. If he attempts to affect an object in a creatures possession, the creature can attempt a Reflex save to negate the effect. If the creature fails the initial saving throw, it immediately drops the item and must attempt a new save each round it attempts to pick up, hold, or use the item. A creature wearing greased armour or clothing gains a +5 circumstance bonus to Acrobatics checks to escape a grapple and a +2 circumstance bonus to its AC against grapple combat manoeuvres.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6EihwtEMpHRNd2o9z_save_effect
attribs.current: Target(s) moves at half speed with a successful DC 10 Acrobatics check.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6EnLCz5FmjEot84p2_description
attribs.current:
Kofehsu touches a target with a device he's holding that uses electricity, requiring a melee attack against the targets EAC. Alternatively, he can instead touch an electrical device a target is wearing (or a target that is an electrical device, such as a robot) with his hand, gaining a +2 bonus to your attack roll. Either way, if his attack hits, the electrical device surges out of control, dealing 4d6 electricity damage to his target.

Casting this spell doesnt provoke attacks of opportunity.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6ErqZv5KlgnZg6grD_target
attribs.current: Up to Three Creatures; No Two of Which Can Be 15 ft. Apart

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6ErqZv5KlgnZg6grD_description
attribs.current:
Kofehsu fires two missiles of magical energy that strike targets unerringly (the creatures must still be valid targets) and deal 1d4+1 damage each. He cant target specific parts of a creature, and objects are not damaged by the spell.

He can target a single creature or several creatures, but each missile can strike only one creature. He must designate targets before he attempts to overcome spell resistance or roll damage.

He can cast this spell as a full action. If he does, he fires three missiles instead of two.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6F7HkUKb00g4Q0eNl_description
attribs.current: You point your finger at the target object, gaining the ability to lift it and move it at will from a distance. As a move action, you can propel the object as far as 15 feet in any direction, though the spell ends if the distance between you and the object ever exceeds the spells range. You cant perform complex operations, such as firing a gun or using a computer, but you can shut a mechanical door or lid and work simple buttons to open or close automated doors or trigger an alarm.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6F7HkUKb00g4Q0eNl_target
attribs.current: One Unattended Object of No More than 10 lbs. or 1 Bulk

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-MU6F9jR7VUSvwgU93U5_description
attribs.current:
Token spells are often some of the first minor changes that spellcasters produce when they begin experimenting with magic. Once cast, token spell enables you to perform simple magical effects for 1 hour. The effects are minor and have severe limitations. Kofehsu can slowly lift one item of light bulk. He can alter items in a 1-foot cube each round, colouring, cleaning, soiling, cooling, warming, or flavouring them. You can create small objects, but they look artificial and are extremely fragile (they cant be used as tools or weapons). He can illuminate an object to shed dim light in a 30-foot radius.

Token spell lacks the power to duplicate any other spell effects. Any actual change to an object (beyond moving, cleaning, or soiling it) persists for only 1 hour.

If the weapon deals two types of damage, both of the damage types become nonlethal. Zidhil can activate or deactivate the merciful fusion as a swift action.

attribs.current: As a standard action, Zidhil can make a charge without the charge penalties (see page 248), and he can substitute a bull rush for the melee attack at the end of the charge.

Merciful
A weapon with the merciful fusion often hums pleasantly when at rest and makes soft, airy musical noises when it is used to make an attack. The magic of this fusion subdues the damaging effect of the weapon it is added to. While this fusion is active, the weapons regular damage becomes nonlethal damage. attribs.current: A shock pad can be installed into an armour upgrade slot. When Kane hits a target with the shock pad, the weapon emits an electric discharge that stuns or damages the target. These weapons are particularly valued in suits of powered armour that bring substantial strength to bear. Shock pads typically are available in static, aurora, storm, and tempest models.

attribs.name: repeating_attack_-MU6JniWA-4t1RrBgt1K_description
attribs.current: Arc rifles fire deadly electrical blasts and have a longer range than arc pistols. Like arc pistols, arc rifles can stun targets that are not killed outright by the electricity damage.

attribs.name: repeating_attack_-MU6JwkcjZSjiKwuivqO_description
attribs.current:
When detonated, a flash grenade releases a pulse of intense radiance.

Explode
Explosives have the explode special property, which lists the amount of damage the explosion deals, the damage type, special effects (with a duration, if necessary), and the radius of the explosion. When Kane attacks with this type of weapon or ammunition, aim at a grid intersection. Each creature within the blast radius takes the listed damage but can attempt a Reflex saving throw for half damage. If the explode special property has any special effects other than damage, they are negated with a successful saving throw. If he scores a critical hit, it applies only to the creature closest to the targeted intersection (he chooses the creature if several are equally close). Some exploding weapons, such as smoke grenades, dont deal damage, so they dont include the damage and damage type entries.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6K9LvvH7hz8ONG6xR_description
attribs.current: The hit-and-run fighting style focuses on tactical movement as Kane moves in and out of combat. He uses ranged weapons but fight close up, and he can even mix ranged and melee attacks. His abilities allow him to move even when he makes full attacks and to avoid getting locked down by his enemies.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6KFre12GY3BZkYh6j_description
attribs.current:
Kane gains Opening Volley as a bonus feat. If he already has this feat, he chooses a bonus combat feat instead. At 9th level, he can use Opening Volley on both his first and second turns in combat.

Benefit: Whenever Kane deals damage to an opponent with a ranged attack on his first turn in a combat, he gains a +2 circumstance bonus to his next melee attack roll against that opponent. This melee attack must occur before the end of his next turn.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6KD8Itm8pCSqEEu1d_description
attribs.current: When Kane makes a full attack, he can also either take a guarded step or move up to half his speed. This movement can come before, between, or after his attacks, but it cant be split up.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6QTP5GfZu3ClVGnyu_description
attribs.current:
A crate fiend dwells within a container as if it were the creatures shell. While inside its container and motionless, a crate fiend appears to be the container. As a move action, a crate fiend can partially or fully withdraw into its shell. If it partially withdraws, it gains partial cover but
takes a 2 penalty to attack rolls and can move at only half speed. While fully withdrawn, the fiend can neither move nor attack but has total cover. The container has AC 10, hardness 10, and 22 Hit Points. The fiend has a 2 penalty to AC in a container that has the broken condition. If the container is destroyed, the penalty increases to 4. A crate fiend can adapt to a new container in 1 hour.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6Q5sc345RhcFZcKo6_description
attribs.current: When a crate fiend dies, as no action on its part, it makes an acid blast attack. The attacks point of origin must be adjacent to the creatures space.

attribs.current: A creature that takes damage from a velstrac cantors claw must succeed at a DC 18 Will saving throw or the pain lingers in its mind, dealing 1d4 additional damage (2d4 if the cantor scored a critical hit) at the start of each of its turns for 1 minute. At the end of each of its turns, the target can attempt another saving throw to end this effect. Each of the cantors additional successful attacks against a creature suffering this effect extends the duration by 1 round. Any form of magical healing ends this effect immediately. This is a mind-affecting effect.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6aYDqOUzU5bhHpQ0o_effect
attribs.current: Suffer [[1d4]] ([[2d4]] if the Cantor scored a Critical Hit) at the start of each turn.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6bEhjiqowbnR4DKlR_description
attribs.current: A cantors appearance causes shock and sympathetic pain. A creature that fails its save against this mind-affecting fear effect is shaken for 1 round.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6bQIiZWcsCjzCc1Iw_description
attribs.current: Once per minute as a full action, a cantor can mouth a soundless scream to create an illusory double of itself that is Large and even more horrifying. Creatures within 30 feet of and able to see the cantor must succeed at a DC 18 Will saving throw or believe this illusory double to be real. At the same moment, the cantor becomes invisible (as per greater invisibility). These effects last as long as at least one creature believes the illusion, but no longer than 1 minute. Both effects also end if the cantor is ever more than 30 feet away from the illusion at the end of its turn. The illusion appears to attack each round on the cantors turn, and the cantor usually attacks the same target, gaining the benefits of both invisibility and stealth. After a creature attacks the illusion, the creature can attempt another save to disbelieve the effect. A creature exposed to this effect is immune to the same cantors waking nightmare for 24 hours.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6bQIiZWcsCjzCc1Iw_effect
attribs.current: Believe in the Double being real.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6Zm8pPoHy1jVrmFcE_description
attribs.current: The Cantor Velstrac precisely identifies a target, such as by name or via a material connection like a personal possession or lock of its hair. The spell fails without expending a spell slot if the target isnt asleep or in a resting state similar to sleep. If it's never met the target in person and lack a material connection to the target, the target gains a +5 bonus to the saving throw. If the spell works, the target remains resting for 1 minute, then has a nightmare, rouses, and becomes frightened for [[2d6]] rounds. The target cant willingly re-enter the affected resting state for 1 hour. To do so after this time has elapsed, the target must succeed at the saving throw again. If this save fails, the target can try again once per hour thereafter. After 24 hours have passed, this restless state ends.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6Zm8pPoHy1jVrmFcE_effect
attribs.current: Becomes roused an frightened for [[2d6]] rounds.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6Zvf7tHoKWSMuKuEt_description
attribs.current: The Cantor Velstrac transforms the matter of its body and any objects it carries or wears into the essence of the Shadow Plane. It is visible as an unattached shadow in bright light or normal light, but it gains total concealment in dim light or darkness (reduced to concealment against creatures that have darkvision). Its body and gear are incorporeal, but it cant fly or pass through solid objects or creatures, and its gear cant be removed from it or used by anyone. It can move at its normal speed along any surface, including horizontal and vertical surfaces and liquids, and difficult terrain doesnt slow it. However, it cant attack physically or manipulate objects. It can speak, cast spells that require no items to cast, and perform mental actions. If it can use spells that have a range of touch and such a spell requires an attack roll, it targets EAC. If it loses consciousness, it and its gear return to your natural form.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6a-JFzh54uFpdfiED_description
attribs.current: The target treats all other creatures as enemies and only itself as an ally. It must attempt attacks of opportunity whenever any creature provokes them. In addition, the target is shaken while adjacent to more than one creature.

attribs.name: repeating_ability_-MU6a-JFzh54uFpdfiED_effect
attribs.current: All creatures become enemies to the target and it becomes shaken while adjacent to more than one creature.
